  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key features typically include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Customer identification requirements\n3. Record-keeping obligations\n4. Implementing internal compliance programs\n5. Screening for high-risk individuals and transactions\n\nMajor regulatory frameworks include:\n- United States Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) international standards\n- Various national banking and financial regulations\n\nFinancial institutions like banks, credit unions, and money transfer services are required to comply with these regulations.",
